{
  "stem": "14897.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And later on, it didn't make any difference, because when you have so little food one of the things that disappears is interest in any sex.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had one child who was born from early encounters in the ghetto who survived and, with his mother, went on to Israel.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I know they survived in Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Her name was Tomkiewicg.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember her first name.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "T-O-M-K-I-E-W-I-C-G.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was boy child, yes, a baby, and he survived.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember at all.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well, it must have been her husband, I imagine.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But maybe he was even conceived before, because I don't remember the father in the camp, and I know that only she survived with the child.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anyway, after we became a group of 600, we were allowed to be together, mixed men and women.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father worked as a doctor, and he sort of apprenticed me, as I was learning to become a nurse.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His duties were to-- to negotiate with the German doctor for the little bit of maybe aspirin or bandages or other things, even a little bit of sulfa drugs that they would give us.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His duties were to decide who was allowed, who was sick and, therefore, was allowed not to come out for the roll call.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because every morning there would be a roll call.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You had to come out and stand in rows and be counted.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the counting would be sometimes a perfunctory affair, taking a few minutes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And sometimes, if for a good or bad reason or whatever, the-- the soldier or officer doing it, usually a noncom sort of, we would be left standing there for half a day, or even a day.",
      "word_count": 37
    }
  ],
